column10: Driver pulled into bike lane to avoid speed bumps, then tailgated very closely behind bike with toddlers in trailer in bike lane, laying on their horn the whole time.

I was running slow (13 min/mi). About to cross Monroe at Hewitt. Stopped and started to walk across. Had one foot in the crosswalk watching a driver driving west. He didn't even touch his brakes. So...I stopped instead of being hit.
At Monroe & Dewitt. Gave driver a “dirty look” (his words) when he almost hit me and my dog in the cross walk. Proceeded to pull a U-turn, roll his windows down, and yell profanities at me.
